  <h1 class="mb-3">Welcome to Your Barrister App</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    This app has been built especially for you — to make your legal work faster, easier, and more organised.
  </p>

  <h2 class="mt-4">Getting Started</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Log in:</strong> Start at the home page and enter the current password.</li>
    <li><strong>Dashboard:</strong> See your to-dos, upcoming matters, and quick access to other tools.</li>
    <li><strong>Create an Attendance Note:</strong> Go to <em>Attendance Notes → New</em>, fill in the client and case details, and save.</li>
    <li><strong>Record Advice:</strong> Use the <em>Record</em> function to dictate a note; the app will transcribe it for you.</li>
    <li><strong>Polish Your Text:</strong> Click <em>Polish</em> to improve grammar and presentation.</li>
    <li><strong>Generate a Report:</strong> Turn any note into a professionally formatted PDF for email or printing.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="mt-4">Main Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Secure access</strong> — password-protected entry.</li>
    <li><strong>Attendance note manager</strong> — draft, final, and sent statuses with archiving.</li>
    <li><strong>Automatic “R v Smith” title generation</strong> from the client’s surname.</li>
    <li><strong>Drop-down selectors</strong> for courts, judges (coram), law firms, and lawyers.</li>
    <li><strong>Expense tracking</strong> with custom categories.</li>
    <li><strong>Next appearance date</strong> tracking and filtering.</li>
    <li><strong>Speech-to-text transcription</strong> via built-in recording.</li>
    <li><strong>PDF export</strong> with polished, professional formatting.</li>
    <li><strong>Transcripts list</strong> with ability to review past recordings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="mt-4">Tips for Best Use</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Update the <em>Status</em> field to keep track of case progress.</li>
    <li>Use the <em>Next appearance date</em> to help you plan and prioritise.</li>
    <li>Archive old notes to keep your main list uncluttered.</li>
    <li>Use the <em>Record</em> function for quick on-the-go dictations.</li>
  </ul>

